# MCP Servers — Setup and Usage

All MCP servers for Cursor and Ollama are managed from a single location:

```
C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\CodingTools\McpServers\
```

## One-Time Setup (all servers at once)

```powershell
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\CodingTools\McpServers\Setup-AllMcpServers\Setup-AllMcpServers.ps1"
```

Detects whether Cursor and/or Ollama is installed, runs all relevant setup scripts, and reports a summary. Restart Cursor after running.

To run setup only (skip tests):
```powershell
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\CodingTools\McpServers\Setup-AllMcpServers\Setup-AllMcpServers.ps1" -SkipTest
```

## Test All Servers

```powershell
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\CodingTools\McpServers\Setup-AllMcpServers\Test-AllMcpServers.ps1"
```

Runs pre-flight checks (mcp.json validation, endpoint connectivity) then tests each server individually.

