## RAG Health Endpoints

Each RAG Python service exposes two health checks on `dedge-server`:

| Endpoint | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `GET /health` | Shallow liveness — process is alive |
| `GET /ready` | Deep readiness — ChromaDB collection is openable (use this to verify the venv is functional) |

```powershell
Invoke-RestMethod "http://dedge-server:8484/ready"  # db2-docs
Invoke-RestMethod "http://dedge-server:8485/ready"  # visual-cobol-docs
Invoke-RestMethod "http://dedge-server:8486/ready"  # Dedge-code
```

---

## How RAG Access Works

RAG services run as Python HTTP servers (NSSM Windows Services) on `dedge-server` (ports 8484-8486). They are unauthenticated. The Cursor MCP proxy (`~/.cursor/rag-proxy/server_mcp_proxy.py`) forwards queries over HTTP, bypassing the C# API entirely.

```
Developer Machine                          dedge-server
┌──────────────────┐                      ┌──────────────────┐
│ Cursor IDE       │                      │ Python HTTP RAGs  │
│  └─ MCP proxy ───┼── HTTP :8484-8486 ──►│  db2-docs         │
│     (stdio)      │                      │  visual-cobol-docs│
│                  │                      │  Dedge-code      │
│ PowerShell       │                      │                   │
│  └─ Ask-Rag ─────┼── HTTP :8484-8486 ──►│  (ChromaDB +      │
│     + Ollama     │                      │   ONNX embedding) │
└──────────────────┘                      └──────────────────┘
```

NSSM services: `AiDocRagDb2` (8484), `AiDocRagCobol` (8485), `AiDocRagCode` (8486)  
Management UI: `http://dedge-server/AiDocNew`  
Registry endpoint: `http://dedge-server:8484/rags`

## If a RAG is broken (HTTP 500 / "No module named 'chromadb'")

The Python venv on the server is missing packages. Run the recovery script:

```powershell
# Via orchestrator (from dev machine)
. "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\CodingTools\Cursor-ServerOrchestrator\_helpers\_CursorAgent.ps1"
Invoke-ServerCommand -ServerName 'dedge-server' `
    -Command '%OptPath%\DedgeWinApps\AiDocNew-Web\scripts\Fix-VenvAndRestart.ps1' `
    -Project 'aidoc-fix' -Timeout 300
```

## Prerequisites

- Windows 11 / Windows Server 2025
- PowerShell 7+ (`pwsh.exe`)
- Python 3.11+ (RAG Cursor setup only)
- Node.js (PostgreSQL MCP setup only)
- Ollama installed from [ollama.com](https://ollama.com) (Ollama setup only)
- Network access to `dedge-server`
